Class BigTwoCard

  • java.lang.Object
    • Card
      • BigTwoCard
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Card>

    public class BigTwoCard
extends Card
    This class is a subclass of Card. It includes a overwritten card comparing method, one following the Big Two game rules. For ranks and suits, we use the following order. From HIGH to LOW: 2, A, K, Q, J, 10, 9, 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3; From HIGH to LOW: Spades ♠ > Hearts ♥ > Clubs ♣ > Diamonds ♦
    Author:
    ali

      • BigTwoCard

        public BigTwoCard(int suit,
                  int rank)
        A constructor to make a Big Two card.
        Parameters:
        suit - An int value [0,3] specifying the the suit of the card:

        0 = Diamond, 1 = Club, 2 = Heart, 3 = Spade

        rank - An int value [0,12] specifying the the rank of the card:

        0 = 'A', 1 = '2', 2 = '3', ..., 8 = '9', 9 = '0', 10 = 'J', 11 = 'Q', 12 = 'K'
